# Sept points pour organiser une CO avec Geco

Don't know where to start? Never use a full-featured O software before? Here is a quick guide to manage an orienteering event: seven steps to handle the race organization. Read on for starters.

1\. Use the [Launcher] and the [Stage] panel to set up a new stage.

2\. Load courses from within the [Stage] panel.

3\. Register competitors from the [Runners] panel and using the [Archive].

> *Voir la démo des points 1 à 3 dans le screencast [Avant la course]().*

4\. Check E-card configuration in the [Stage] panel and click the Reader button in the [Toolbar].

Runners download their e-card in the reader to check their status and get their split times.

4bis. Resolve problems directly in the [Runners] panel and using the [Merge] dialog read [Workflows](../howtos/index.html) to get a better a picture of manual vs auto modes).

> *Découvrez le mode auto dans ce [screencast]().*

5\. Print intermediate [Results].

> *Voir la démo des points 4 à 5 dans le screencast [Pendant la course]().*

6\. Don't forget to check [unresolved statuses](../howtos/endstage.fr.html) to see if everyone is finished.

7\. Generate final [Results] for publishing and analysis.

> *Voir la démo des points 6 et 7 dans le screencast [Fin de course]().*

